## [CRITICAL] Version Constraints — DO NOT MODIFY

- PHP: 8.4.18 (FORBIDDEN: upgrade to 8.5+)
- Laravel: 11.51.0 (FORBIDDEN: major update)
- Filament: 3.3.49 (FORBIDDEN: v4 API or Schema patterns)
- composer.json: NEVER change versions without explicit user approval
- Sail runtime path: ./vendor/laravel/sail/runtimes/8.4 (fixed, do not alter)
- compose.yaml: preserve structure and indentation exactly

## [RULE] Color contrast (always)

- Every background MUST have explicit foreground colors that remain readable in both light and dark (use `text-gray-950 dark:text-white` or a dedicated palette such as `bg-slate-900` + `text-slate-100`).
- Never leave body text as default without checking: `bg-white` + `text-gray-900` / `dark:bg-gray-900` + `text-gray-100` (or equivalent) on the same element or its text children.
- Custom modals/panels: either force a single contrast context (e.g. `dark` + dark `!bg-*` + light text) or duplicate Filament’s light/dark pairs; do not mix white Filament surfaces with theme-dependent text that can match the background.
- After UI changes, mentally verify: light mode AND dark mode — no “invisible” text on tables, inputs, badges, or nested `fi-section` cards.

## [RULE] Filament v3 Frontend (Admin Panel)

- USE: x-filament::_ and x-filament-tables::_ official Blade components
- FORBIDDEN: custom <div>/<table> layouts, inline styles, <style> tags
- CSS: Tailwind utility classes only
- DO NOT break Filament-generated class structures (fi-section, fi-input-wrp, etc.)

## [RULE] Compact UI

- Reduce default spacing by one step (e.g. gap-y-4 → gap-y-2)
- Remove empty fi-section-header via header(null)
- Prefer table layout over card layout for list views
- Use grid for horizontal input layout; avoid tall vertical pages
- Responsive grid: grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3

## [RULE] Robustness

- Live inputs (Admin Panel): wire:model.live.debounce.500ms required. (See High Latency rules below for POS exceptions).
- Numeric inputs: numeric + step="0.001"
- Images/large elements: aspect-video + overflow-hidden
- On layout issues: replace custom implementation with standard Filament components first

## [RULE] Frontend Layout Safety (No-Drift)

- One page, one CSS ecosystem: NEVER mix Bootstrap and Tailwind on the same page.
- If a page uses any `x-filament::*` component, ALWAYS include `@filamentStyles` and `@filamentScripts(withCore: true)`.
- Keep Tailwind syntax version consistent per project setup (do not mix v3/v4 utility names).
- Prefer `@vite(resources/css/app.css)` for stable class generation; use CDN only when explicitly required.
- Keep layout responsibilities isolated (e.g. `timecard` layout must not depend on Bootstrap-only nav/modal components).
- Standardize form controls: use consistent classes for `input/select/textarea`; for `select`, enforce `appearance-none` + custom arrow.
- Keep Alpine.js local and minimal (`x-data` scoped per section; use `x-show` + `x-collapse` for toggles) **EXCEPT for POS/Guest UI**.
- Do not put complex data logic in Blade; compute in Controller/Livewire and pass view-ready data **EXCEPT for POS/Guest UI local drafts**.
- Before finalizing UI changes, verify mobile (390px) and tablet (768px) for: initial render, input, error state, modal state, and navigation.
- Final grep check for Tailwind pages: no `btn-`, `row`, `col-`, `data-bs-`, or Bootstrap CDN links.

## [RULE] High Latency Environment Architecture (POS & Guest UI) - CRITICAL

- NO CHATTY LIVEWIRE REQUESTS: Do NOT use `wire:click` or `wire:model` for intermediate UI states (e.g., selecting items, toggling toppings, adding items to a draft cart). Every network request costs hundreds of milliseconds.
- USE ALPINE.JS FOR LOCAL DRAFTS: Overriding the "minimal Alpine" rule, POS/Guest UI MUST manage draft states entirely client-side using `x-data`. Think like a SPA.
- BULK MUTATIONS: Send aggregated data arrays to Livewire in a single bulk request (`$wire.bulkSubmit(drafts)`).
- OPTIMISTIC UI UPDATES: UI MUST react instantly using Alpine.js (e.g., `x-on:click="open = false; setTimeout(()=> $wire.submit(), 50)"`). Do NOT wait for Livewire response cycles to close modals.

## [RULE] TALL Stack Hydration & State Safety (Guest UI)

- REQUIRED (Livewire 3 guest / full-page components): The Blade view’s **first literal HTML tag** must be the Livewire root you expect to carry `wire:id` (e.g. `#guest-order-root`). Livewire injects `wire:id` only into that first tag (`Livewire\Drawer\Utils::insertAttributesIntoHtmlRoot`). If `<script>` or any other tag comes first, `wire:id` attaches there and `Livewire.find` + `guest-order-root` break (e.g. “Service unavailable” on submit). Put `<script type="application/json" id="guest-order-data">` **inside** that root element, not before it.
- FORBIDDEN: Injecting JSON data (`@json`, `@js`) directly into HTML attributes like `x-data` or `x-init`. It causes double-quote collision and DOM breakage.
- REQUIRED: Use `<script type="application/json" id="data-xxx">` to pass large PHP arrays/objects to the frontend safely.
- FORBIDDEN: `import Alpine from 'alpinejs'` in standard JS files when using Livewire 3 (causes double instantiation).
- REQUIRED: Extend Alpine only via `document.addEventListener('alpine:init', () => { window.Alpine.store(...) })`.
- REQUIRED: Ensure Tailwind v4 content scanning is configured via `@source` in `resources/css/app.css`, not `tailwind.config.js`.

## [RULE] POS SPA-Hybrid Three Inviolable Principles（不可侵原則・変更禁止）

This project pursues SPA-like UX on a high-latency link (Tunisia ↔ OVH Europe).
The following three principles MUST hold simultaneously. Any change that violates
even one of them is forbidden — they are the structural firewall against the
Phase 2 failure (where draft accumulation in Alpine led to dual-source drift,
DOM breakage, and "store にためれば速くなる" misconception).

1. **WRITES ALWAYS GO THROUGH LIVEWIRE / DB**
   - Adding, editing, or deleting order lines / sessions / discounts MUST be
     performed via Livewire actions (DB write first, then UI update).
   - FORBIDDEN: accumulating mutations in Alpine state and reconciling later.
   - FORBIDDEN: any `addItem` / `removeItem` / `_persist` style API on Alpine
     stores that hold business data.

2. **ALPINE CACHE IS READ-ONLY AFTERIMAGE (残像) ONLY**
   - Alpine may hold a thin, read-only snapshot of *recently viewed* server
     state purely for instant context switching (e.g., last N tables' line
     lists shown as a placeholder while Livewire re-fetches).
   - The authoritative source for displayed business data (order lines,
     prices, totals, KDS status) is ALWAYS the Livewire component
     (`posOrders` etc.). Alpine values are overwritten on every Livewire
     response.
   - The cache MUST be visually marked as "syncing" (e.g., dim/badge) until
     the matching Livewire payload arrives and confirms it.

3. **A SYNC BUTTON ALWAYS EXISTS AS THE ESCAPE HATCH**
   - The POS UI MUST provide a visible "🔄 Sync" control that forces a fresh
     fetch from Livewire/DB and overwrites the read-only cache.
   - Sync MUST NOT clear in-progress draft inputs (e.g., addModal fields).
   - Sync is the contractually-promised path to the latest truth — staff are
     trained to press it whenever in doubt or after multi-device operations.

Operational consequence:
- The `posDraft` Alpine store is restricted to context switching and
  read-only afterimage cache. It MUST NOT carry mutation APIs.
- Any future "let's just keep it in Alpine to make it faster" proposal is
  rejected by these principles.

## [RULE] POS Read-Only Cache & Sync Button（残像キャッシュと同期運用）

Implementation rules derived from the three inviolable principles above.

### Cache shape & lifetime

- Scope: last 3–5 tables most recently opened in this browser tab.
- Storage: in-memory Alpine store (preferred). `sessionStorage` allowed only
  if scoped to a single tab and cleared on logout / shop switch.
  `localStorage` is FORBIDDEN for line data (cross-tab drift risk).
- Eviction: LRU on table count; per-entry soft-TTL of 60 seconds (after
  which the "syncing" badge becomes prominent even if a payload arrives).
- Content: minimal fields needed for placeholder render only
  (line id, item name, qty, options summary, total). No mutation hooks.

### Switch behaviour (right pane)

- On table tap:
  - If cache hit → render afterimage immediately + show "🔄 同期中…" badge.
  - If cache miss → render skeleton placeholder (never blank).
- On Livewire payload arrival:
  - `posOrders` overwrites the displayed lines (authoritative).
  - The cache entry for that table is updated from the payload.
  - The "同期中…" badge is removed.

### Sync button (mandatory UI)

- Placement: visible at all times in the POS table dashboard header.
- Action: triggers a Livewire fetch that refreshes the active table and
  invalidates / refreshes all cache entries; MUST NOT touch in-progress
  draft form fields.
- Auto-trigger conditions (system-side safety net, in addition to manual
  press):
  - Browser tab regains visibility (`visibilitychange` → visible).
  - Same table tapped twice consecutively.
  - Cache entry exceeds soft-TTL while displayed.

### Forbidden patterns

- FORBIDDEN: writing user mutations into the cache (the cache is read-only).
- FORBIDDEN: using the cache as the source of totals, KDS status, or any
  value that influences money or kitchen flow.
- FORBIDDEN: hydrating the cache via `@json` / `@js` inside `x-data` /
  `x-init` attributes — use `<script type="application/json" id="...">`
  or assign from Livewire response payloads.
- FORBIDDEN: extending the cache to hold draft order lines (that is the
  Phase 2 anti-pattern).

### Staff-facing operating rule (to be communicated)

- 「テーブル切替は前回の残像が一瞬出ます」
- 「他端末の最新状況を見たいときは 🔄 Sync を押す」
- 「入力途中で Sync を押しても入力は消えません」

## [RULE] POS Draft Store 責務（旧ルール — 上記 SPA-Hybrid 三原則に統合済み）

- The previous "POS Draft Store 責務" rule is superseded by, and fully
  contained in, "[RULE] POS SPA-Hybrid Three Inviolable Principles" and
  "[RULE] POS Read-Only Cache & Sync Button" above.
- Concretely retained constraints:
  - `posDraft` store role: table-switch context + read-only afterimage cache
    only.
  - FORBIDDEN: adding `addItem` / `removeItem` / `_persist` APIs.
  - Authoritative display source remains `posOrders` (Livewire).
  - Item creation: `submitAddLine` writes to DB immediately; never queued
    in Alpine.

